FBIS4-21862 "jptot015__l94027" JPRS-TOT-94-015-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 5 April 1994 LATIN AMERICA HONDURAS Armed Forces Thwart Alleged Plan To Assassinate President Armed Forces Thwart Alleged Plan To Assassinate President PA0504195294 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 1903 GMT 5 Apr 94 PA0504195294 Panama City ACAN Spanish BFN [Text] Tegucigalpa, 5 Apr (ACAN-EFE) -- The Honduran Armed Forces thwarted an alleged plan which would reportedly be executed by three Nicaraguan citizens to assassinate President Carlos Roberto Reina. Army Spokesman Colonel Napoleon Santos announced today military intelligence learned about the plan after Nicaraguan citizens Luis Enrique Quintero, Santiago Rivas, and Roger Arguello entered the country on 7 March. According to the high-ranking military officer, who said Enrique Quintero was a member of the intelligence department of the Sandinist People's Army (EPS), the three Nicaraguan citizens had planned to burn a paint factory and kidnap three businessmen.
